The paper discusses the use of soft constraints in artificial intelligence, which is a topic commonly associated with the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also addresses the computational complexity of finding the optimal solution to a collection of soft constraints, which is a problem that falls under the scope of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CC (computational complexity). The paper's focus on identifying a tractable class of soft binary constraints suggests a connection to cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
